Miscellaneous federal excise taxes are imposed by the Revenue Act of
                                1932 on telegraph, telephone, radio and cable facilities; admission,
                                dues and initiation fees; transfers of stocks and bonds;
                                conveyances; sales of produce for future delivery; passage tickets;
                                foreign insurance policies; safe deposit boxes; checks; electrical
                                energy and use of boats.

